Package: grass
Type: Package
Title: Prevalence-Aware Interpretation of Binary Inter-Rater Agreement
Version: 0.1.2
Authors@R: c(
    person("Austin", "Semmel", email = "runfast031@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Rachel", "Gidaro", role = "aut"))
Description: Computes Cohen's kappa, PABAK (prevalence- and bias-adjusted
    kappa), and Gwet's AC1 for binary inter-rater agreement, and interprets
    them against simulation-derived, prevalence-conditioned thresholds from
    the GRASS framework (Guide for Rater Agreement under Structural Skew).
    Standard interpretation schemes, such as Landis and Koch (1977), apply a
    single fixed threshold regardless of prevalence; this is known to misclassify
    rater quality at skewed prevalences. The package provides compute, evaluate,
    plot, and threshold-lookup functions with a single interface that accepts
    wide, long, paired, or 2x2 count input.
